APE KEYS(1)                                                        APE KEYS(1)



NNAAMMEE
       APE - Another Programmer's Editor

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ape -h[elp]
       ape [file1] [file2] ... [fileN]
       xape [-m] [file1] [file2] ... [fileN]


CCoonnvveennttiioonnss
       <key1>-<key2>  means  press  and  release  key1, then press and release
       key2.

       <key1>+<key2> means press key2 while holding down key1.


PPoopp--ddoowwnn MMeennuuss
       Display a pop-down  menu:  <<AAlltt>>++<<hhiilliigghhtteedd  lleetttteerr>>  or  "<Esc>-<high-
       lighted letter>"

       Next menu: <<rriigghhtt aarrrrooww>>

       Previous menu: <<lleefftt aarrrrooww>>


MMeennuu hhoott--kkeeyyss
       Save file: <<CCttrrll++ss>> or <<EEsscc>>--<<EEsscc>>

       Toggle displayed file: <<CCttrrll>>++tt

       Find word: <<CCttrrll>>++ff or <<EEsscc>>--//

       Repeat last find: <<CCttrrll>>++nn or <<FF33>>

       Compile to object: <<FF66>>

       Build and run: <<EEsscc>>--rr or <<FF55>>

       Goto next error: <<EEsscc>>--nn

       Help on word under cursor: <<FF11>>


CCuurrssoorr mmoottiioonn
       Move Left: <<LLeefftt aarrrrooww>>

       Move Right: <<RRiigghhtt aarrrrooww>>

       Move Up: <<UUpp aarrrrooww>>

       Move Down: <<DDoowwnn aarrrrooww>>

       Beginning of next line: <<EEnntteerr>> (works only in replace mode)

       Next word: <<CCttrrll>>++ww

       Previous word: <<CCttrrll>>++pp

       End of line: <<CCttrrll>>++ee or <<EEnndd>>

       Beginning of line: <<CCttrrll>>++bb or <<HHoommee>>

       Next page: <<PPaaggee DDoowwnn>> or <<CCttrrll>>++yy

       Previous page: <<PPaaggee UUpp>> or <<CCttrrll>>++uu

       Top line of file: <<EEsscc>>--tt

       Last line of file: <<EEsscc>>--ll

       Goto a line #: <<CCttrrll>>++gg


IInnsseerrttiinngg aanndd ddeelleettiinngg
       Toggle insert/replace mode: <<IInnsseerrtt>> or <<CCttrrll>>++rr

       Delete character at cursor position: <<DDeelleettee>> or <<CCttrrll>>++dd

       Delete  character left of cursor: <<BBaacckkssppaaccee>> or <<CCttrrll>>++hh ( Note: Check
       your terminal emulator settings if backspace acts like Del.  Many  ter-
       minal emulators can be configured to send either BS or DEL, and it must
       be set to match the terminfo entry for your terminal. )

       Delelete to end of word: <<CCttrrll>>++oo

       Delete to end of line: <<CCttrrll>>++kk

       Delete a line: <<CCttrrll>>++xx

       Undelete line: <<CCttrrll>>++zz


CCuuttttiinngg aanndd ppaassttiinngg
       Begin marking area:

       Move to beginning or area and type <<FF44>> or <<EEsscc>>--mm

       End marking area:

       Move to end of area and type <<FF44>> or <<EEsscc>>--mm again.

       Delete marked area: <<CCttrrll>>++xx

       Paste marked area: <<CCttrrll>>++vv

       Cancel marked area: <<FF44>> or <<EEsscc>>--mm

       Invoke an edit macro: <<FF99>> or <<EEsscc>>--EEnntteerr

       Join next line to current: <<ccttrrll>>++ee or <<HHoommee>> followed by <<ddeell>>


MMiisscceellllaanneeoouuss
       Scroll so that current line is at top of window: <<EEsscc>>--aa

       Redraw screen: <<CCttrrll>>++ll




                                                                   APE KEYS(1)
